-- Spencer Spirit to buy retailer Brookstone as part of bankruptcy plan
-- By Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 09:30AM EDT
-- None



April 3 (Reuters) - Specialty retailer Brookstone Inc [TEMSHB.UL] said it would be bought by Spencer Spirit Holdings Inc [SPCST.UL] for about $147 million as part of a prepackaged bankruptcy protection plan.

Brookstone sells products ranging from massage chairs to bathroom slippers and operates more than 300 stores throughout the United States and Puerto Rico. [ID:nGNXVAFIKa]